  <name>am-okay</name>
  <summary>The `am-okay` program allows dynamically to copy/move files/directories (via the terminal)</summary>
  
  <metadata_license>MIT</metadata_license>
  <project_license>GPL-2.0-or-later</project_license>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      The <code>am-okay</code> program allows to copy or move files or directories in a dynamic mode via a console (terminal).
    </p>
    <p>
      With the <code>am-okay</code> program, you can dynamically copy or move files or directories where access is permitted. The program itself partly imitates the Linux <code>cp</code> , <code>mv</code> commands but dynamically. You can tag files or  directories as items to copy or move via a console (terminal), and paste these items via another  console (terminal).
    </p>
    <p>
      A lot of actions are possible, you can even tag files or directories in arrays and paste them  wherever you want in your Linux system.
    </p>
  </description>
  
